---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TrustStrip from '../components/TrustStrip.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Little Boracay Calatagan, Batangas"
  description="About Little Boracay — the natural sandbar destination in Calatagan, Batangas and LittleBoracay.com, the dedicated travel resource for visitors."
>
<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="overline">About</span>
    <h1>About Little Boracay</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Little Boracay Calatagan is a premier sandbar destination in Batangas — and LittleBoracay.com is your dedicated guide to experiencing it.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<TrustStrip />
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-layout">
      <div>
        <h2 class="section-title">About the Destination</h2>
        <p><strong>Little Boracay</strong> is a natural tidal sandbar located off the western coastline of Calatagan, Batangas, Philippines, facing the South China Sea. Known for its crystal-clear shallow waters, wide white sand areas, and iconic floating bamboo cottages anchored offshore, the destination has become one of the most popular coastal escapes for travelers from Metro Manila and Batangas.</p>
        <p>The sandbar sits within the coastal municipality of Calatagan — a growing tourism area in southern Luzon known for its beaches, fishing communities, and relaxed coastal atmosphere. Little Boracay draws visitors for day trips, family outings, group celebrations, and photography.</p>
        <p>The beauty of Little Boracay lies in its natural, undeveloped character. Unlike resort beaches, Little Boracay is shaped by the tides — the sandbar appears and changes throughout the day, creating an ever-shifting landscape that rewards visitors who time their arrival well.</p>

        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:40px;">About LittleBoracay.com</h2>
        <p><strong>LittleBoracay.com</strong> is the dedicated online platform for information about Little Boracay in Calatagan, Batangas. As interest in the sandbar grows, travelers increasingly search for reliable, up-to-date information about how to visit, what to expect, and how to book.</p>
        <p>LittleBoracay.com was created to be that resource — a centralized, accurate, and helpful guide for anyone planning a trip to the Little Boracay sandbar, alongside a booking and inquiry platform to help visitors connect directly with local operators.</p>

        <div class="vision-box">
          <h3>Our Vision</h3>
          <p>To be the most trusted online resource for Little Boracay — helping travelers explore the sandbar while supporting responsible tourism and awareness of Calatagan's coastal communities.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:36px;margin-bottom:16px;">Connect With the Community</h3>
